1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:06,001
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,215 --> 00:00:40,545
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:45,215 --> 00:00:47,185
(Episode 6)

5
00:00:55,325 --> 00:00:56,725
What a pair...

6
00:01:07,705 --> 00:01:08,705
What's this for?

7
00:01:09,505 --> 00:01:10,505
Are you making flower pancakes?

8
00:01:11,205 --> 00:01:12,575
Did Director Shin ask for them?

9
00:01:13,445 --> 00:01:14,615
Or are you just making them?

10
00:01:19,685 --> 00:01:22,655
Are you all ignoring me?
Is Director Shin your only deity now?

11
00:01:25,995 --> 00:01:28,295
You too? Hey, Lee Shim!

12
00:01:30,295 --> 00:01:31,295
Park Soo!

13
00:01:34,995 --> 00:01:36,865
I can fire you both.

14
00:01:43,445 --> 00:01:48,345
I'll be the one making
Director Shin's birthday dinner this time.

15
00:01:52,755 --> 00:01:54,385
Don't you two work well together...

16
00:01:55,085 --> 00:01:56,085
Why not just get married?

17
00:01:57,285 --> 00:01:58,285
Who's the senior here?

18
00:01:59,625 --> 00:02:00,625
Lee Shim.

19
00:02:02,295 --> 00:02:03,295
How old are you?

20
00:02:05,195 --> 00:02:06,895
It's impossible to tell her age.

21
00:02:13,605 --> 00:02:15,805
You all have no manners.

22
00:02:23,785 --> 00:02:25,985
I looked into it,
and on that day, two babies...

23
00:02:26,755 --> 00:02:27,755
Yes...

24
00:02:35,425 --> 00:02:36,425
But...

25
00:02:38,565 --> 00:02:40,095
I don't think it's you.

26
00:02:41,265 --> 00:02:42,335
I just have a feeling.

27
00:02:42,865 --> 00:02:44,765
You don't resemble my family at all.

28
00:02:46,735 --> 00:02:49,375
Family members don't always
have to look alike.

29
00:02:51,405 --> 00:02:53,645
What about the other child
left at the church that day?

30
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:55,845
- Yes.
- Can you get in touch with her?

31
00:02:57,585 --> 00:02:58,585
Yes.

32
00:02:59,715 --> 00:03:03,455
Could you explain the situation
and arrange for me to meet them?

33
00:03:04,855 --> 00:03:07,125
Yes, but shouldn't we get a test done?

34
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:09,025
I'll meet her first.

35
00:03:09,525 --> 00:03:11,325
If I feel she isn't the one either...

36
00:03:16,105 --> 00:03:17,635
What's her name?

37
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:20,235
Kim Jin Ju.

38
00:03:20,805 --> 00:03:21,975
We even have the same last name.

39
00:03:26,145 --> 00:03:27,815
I'd like to call her now.

40
00:03:28,615 --> 00:03:29,615
I'll try calling her.

41
00:03:31,585 --> 00:03:33,885
(Kim Jin Ju)

42
00:03:35,855 --> 00:03:37,825
The phone is turned off.

43
00:03:37,885 --> 00:03:39,755
Please leave a message after the tone.

44
00:03:39,825 --> 00:03:40,895
She must be working.

45
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:42,565
Her phone's off.

46
00:03:45,525 --> 00:03:47,495
- What does she do?
- Jin Ju?

47
00:03:47,565 --> 00:03:49,635
- Yes.
- She's a stylist.

48
00:03:49,765 --> 00:03:53,875
- Like celebrity outfits?
- Yes.

49
00:03:56,705 --> 00:03:58,205
And where did she go to school?

50
00:03:58,675 --> 00:04:01,345
You can ask her that in person.

51
00:04:12,555 --> 00:04:15,025
You seem to have a job too.

52
00:04:15,295 --> 00:04:16,395
Yes.

53
00:04:16,465 --> 00:04:19,235
- Where do you work?
- The culture desk at Sungwoo Daily.

54
00:04:21,095 --> 00:04:22,095
You're a reporter?

55
00:04:22,565 --> 00:04:24,935
Yes. And you?

56
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,305
I was away...

57
00:04:27,435 --> 00:04:29,145
this year for a while.

58
00:04:29,945 --> 00:04:33,315
When Kim Jin Ju gets in touch,
could you give her my number?

59
00:04:34,645 --> 00:04:36,345
Okay. But...

60
00:04:37,445 --> 00:04:40,015
you really don't think it's me?

61
00:04:42,985 --> 00:04:44,755
Do you want me to be your dad?

62
00:04:47,525 --> 00:04:49,895
I need to meet everyone to know for sure.

63
00:04:59,675 --> 00:05:01,775
They're treating him
like he's absolute royalty.

64
00:05:05,715 --> 00:05:07,075
I don't eat carbs.

65
00:05:19,255 --> 00:05:20,595
Did you say you wanted to eat these?

66
00:05:22,195 --> 00:05:24,395
It's because I remember how my mom
used to make them for me...

67
00:05:24,965 --> 00:05:25,965
around this time of year.

68
00:05:28,095 --> 00:05:31,205
So your comfort food is azalea pancakes?

69
00:05:32,435 --> 00:05:33,475
For me,

70
00:05:34,305 --> 00:05:35,975
it's chive and pumpkin pancakes.

71
00:05:37,745 --> 00:05:39,375
I hate the word "bindaetteok."

72
00:05:39,875 --> 00:05:42,545
It just sounds so destitute and poor.

73
00:05:43,785 --> 00:05:45,785
I'll make your birthday dinner this time.

74
00:05:45,915 --> 00:05:48,055
Something really special and grand.

75
00:05:48,655 --> 00:05:49,655
We'll invite your friends.

76
00:05:49,985 --> 00:05:50,985
I'm busy.

77
00:05:51,385 --> 00:05:52,395
And it's too much trouble.

78
00:05:52,925 --> 00:05:55,125
Still, you should have
at least one proper meal.

79
00:05:56,895 --> 00:05:58,265
Shouldn't you be resting in bed?

80
00:05:58,765 --> 00:05:59,765
I'm much better now.

81
00:06:00,365 --> 00:06:01,635
I've pulled a muscle before.

82
00:06:02,065 --> 00:06:03,205
Right.

83
00:06:03,705 --> 00:06:04,865
It wasn't this body.

84
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:08,905
What dishes do you miss the most
made by your mother?

85
00:06:10,075 --> 00:06:11,075
Meat and rice.

86
00:06:11,445 --> 00:06:13,715
Meat and rice? How do you make it?

87
00:06:13,845 --> 00:06:16,685
Even when Nurse Park uses prime beef,
it just doesn't taste the same.

88
00:06:16,685 --> 00:06:18,015
Although it might look the same.

89
00:06:19,015 --> 00:06:21,215
When will you stop being so formal?

90
00:06:21,485 --> 00:06:22,725
It's going to become a habit.

91
00:06:23,585 --> 00:06:24,585
What if someone hears you?

92
00:06:27,395 --> 00:06:28,395
I'll get there.

93
00:06:29,995 --> 00:06:31,395
I know men can't keep secrets.

94
00:06:31,395 --> 00:06:33,165
Are you telling Ha Yong Joong everything?

95
00:06:35,195 --> 00:06:37,305
It's always the ones closest to you
who betray you.

96
00:06:39,735 --> 00:06:40,805
Hey.

97
00:06:41,075 --> 00:06:43,445
You called? I'm out working.

98
00:06:44,475 --> 00:06:45,505
This time,

99
00:06:46,945 --> 00:06:49,345
you might actually get to meet
your biological dad.

100
00:06:49,885 --> 00:06:51,045
Is someone looking for me again?

101
00:06:51,545 --> 00:06:53,515
The Self-Reliance Center director
contacted me.

102
00:06:54,415 --> 00:06:56,555
So, I met a man named Kim Gwang Cheol.

103
00:06:56,555 --> 00:06:57,785
Kim Jin Ju!

104
00:06:58,685 --> 00:06:59,895
You're not done yet?

105
00:07:00,295 --> 00:07:01,455
I have two scenes left.

106
00:07:01,455 --> 00:07:03,225
I'm the last one off,

107
00:07:03,225 --> 00:07:04,465
so I don't think I'll be done
until after 1 a.m.

108
00:07:04,725 --> 00:07:07,995
The news stories drop at dawn,
so I need to get to sleep now.

109
00:07:08,635 --> 00:07:10,265
- Tomorrow, then?
- Okay.

110
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:31,625
James!

111
00:07:36,825 --> 00:07:38,495
Hey, you're here.

112
00:07:40,165 --> 00:07:41,165
What is all this?

113
00:07:41,935 --> 00:07:43,305
A monk I know...

114
00:07:43,565 --> 00:07:45,065
What about a monk?
Did he give this to you?

115
00:07:45,535 --> 00:07:47,105
- Yes.
- Why?

116
00:07:47,835 --> 00:07:48,905
Are you hungry?

117
00:07:48,975 --> 00:07:50,745
Let's have breakfast. It's been a while.

118
00:07:51,105 --> 00:07:52,405
It'll just take 30 minutes.

119
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:06,155
Why did he tell you to do this?

120
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:08,695
I told him I had insomnia.

121
00:08:08,695 --> 00:08:10,325
Does it work? Are you sleeping?

122
00:08:10,895 --> 00:08:11,895
Yes.

123
00:08:12,295 --> 00:08:13,495
So is this the logic?

124
00:08:13,495 --> 00:08:16,265
When you get sleep paralysis,
the spirits see this and can't get you?

125
00:08:16,905 --> 00:08:18,505
Want rice or toast?

126
00:08:30,215 --> 00:08:32,485
So you gave the painting
to Ba Ra after all.

127
00:08:33,885 --> 00:08:34,885
No.

128
00:08:37,355 --> 00:08:39,955
"Do you want to take it back
and continue our relationship?"

129
00:08:40,025 --> 00:08:42,795
"Or should I take the artwork,
and we go our separate ways?"

130
00:08:42,865 --> 00:08:45,165
When she puts it like that, what can I do?
I had to take it back.

131
00:08:45,595 --> 00:08:48,195
She even rejects you in a lovely way,
making you feel good about it.

132
00:08:48,435 --> 00:08:49,605
Don't take it too far.

133
00:08:49,665 --> 00:08:51,005
Even if I don't,

134
00:08:51,435 --> 00:08:52,835
you know what they say,

135
00:08:52,835 --> 00:08:54,575
"You can't hide love, poverty,
or a cough."

136
00:08:54,835 --> 00:08:55,945
Hide it.

137
00:08:55,945 --> 00:08:57,575
If you cause trouble by being selfish,

138
00:08:58,305 --> 00:09:00,015
I'll be really disappointed in you.

139
00:09:05,115 --> 00:09:06,715
I'm saying this because it's us.

140
00:09:06,715 --> 00:09:09,555
I don't think of Professor Lee
or Professor Shin as someone I'd marry.

141
00:09:09,755 --> 00:09:11,525
It's just for a bit of fun,
a passing interest.

142
00:09:12,855 --> 00:09:16,265
Reporter Geum may be smart
and have the looks and pedigree,

143
00:09:16,525 --> 00:09:18,895
but would just any family accept her
as a daughter-in-law?

144
00:09:22,365 --> 00:09:25,835
The age gap aside, she's perfect for me.

145
00:09:25,835 --> 00:09:27,005
We're kindred spirits.

146
00:09:27,605 --> 00:09:30,775
Age doesn't matter these days,
as long as you don't look old.

147
00:09:31,075 --> 00:09:32,105
You think you can control that?

148
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:35,575
We have the world's best cosmetic tech.

149
00:09:35,645 --> 00:09:36,885
It's too late for you.

150
00:09:37,185 --> 00:09:38,345
They'll say you're going senile.

151
00:09:38,345 --> 00:09:40,515
Don't you know what people look for
in a marriage prospect?

152
00:09:40,585 --> 00:09:42,515
I don't. All I know is love.

153
00:09:42,825 --> 00:09:44,285
So you think it's best just to rip
the band-aid off?

154
00:09:44,285 --> 00:09:46,095
Then go on and confess everything to her.

155
00:09:46,525 --> 00:09:48,995
You'll probably never see her again.

156
00:09:49,465 --> 00:09:50,525
Want to bet?

157
00:09:52,025 --> 00:09:54,895
He said he doesn't think it's me.
I don't look alike at all.

158
00:09:55,135 --> 00:09:56,865
What does he look like?
His clothes and everything.

159
00:09:57,965 --> 00:09:59,775
- He's just average.
- You mean shabby?

160
00:10:00,375 --> 00:10:01,375
No.

161
00:10:01,575 --> 00:10:03,775
But we were the only two babies left...

162
00:10:04,045 --> 00:10:06,045
at that church on December 21, 1999.

163
00:10:06,445 --> 00:10:08,645
You have the same last name as him,
so it has to be you.

164
00:10:09,845 --> 00:10:10,845
I'm so nervous.

165
00:10:11,185 --> 00:10:12,615
I'll text you his number.

166
00:11:13,545 --> 00:11:14,775
Kim Jin Ju?

167
00:11:16,045 --> 00:11:17,045
Yes.

168
00:11:30,765 --> 00:11:32,265
An iced Americano, please.

169
00:11:32,665 --> 00:11:34,295
- Same for me.
- Okay.

170
00:11:35,835 --> 00:11:37,435
We don't even need a DNA test.

171
00:11:38,305 --> 00:11:41,575
You're the spitting image of the mother
you've never even met.

172
00:11:42,305 --> 00:11:43,305
Really?

173
00:11:45,175 --> 00:11:46,245
Do you have a picture?

174
00:11:49,145 --> 00:11:50,145
You don't?

175
00:11:51,045 --> 00:11:52,315
I don't have one.

176
00:11:53,985 --> 00:11:55,715
We weren't married.

177
00:11:56,185 --> 00:11:57,185
What was your relationship, exactly?

178
00:11:57,725 --> 00:11:59,555
So you just dated and then broke up?

179
00:11:59,955 --> 00:12:02,355
Or were you already married
when you met her,

180
00:12:02,965 --> 00:12:05,525
- and I was the result of an affair?
- No.

181
00:12:05,895 --> 00:12:07,635
We dated for about a year.

182
00:12:07,835 --> 00:12:10,705
When we drifted apart,
I didn't even know she was pregnant.

183
00:12:12,705 --> 00:12:13,705
How...

184
00:12:15,605 --> 00:12:17,045
I didn't know...

185
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:20,415
Her name was Hwang Mi Sook.

186
00:12:21,445 --> 00:12:24,085
- My birth mother?
- Yes.

187
00:12:24,685 --> 00:12:27,285
She left you with my mother
and then disappeared.

188
00:12:28,155 --> 00:12:30,155
- So...
- Then who threw me away...

189
00:12:30,555 --> 00:12:31,755
in the box at Minjin Church?

190
00:12:33,795 --> 00:12:36,095
- I wouldn't say threw away...
- But that's what it was.

191
00:12:38,565 --> 00:12:40,335
I only found out later.

192
00:12:40,835 --> 00:12:41,995
Then my grandmother did it?

193
00:12:42,765 --> 00:12:45,835
Let's not speak ill of the dead.

194
00:12:47,205 --> 00:12:48,535
Her own flesh-and-blood granddaughter?

195
00:12:48,905 --> 00:12:50,145
Given her circumstances,

196
00:12:50,545 --> 00:12:52,175
how could an old woman raise you all
on her own?

197
00:12:53,175 --> 00:12:54,715
Then what were you doing?

198
00:12:56,245 --> 00:12:58,645
Do people only raise kids and grandkids
when things are easy?

199
00:12:59,285 --> 00:13:00,915
That was a long time ago.

200
00:13:01,585 --> 00:13:04,855
- Does the past really matter?
- "The past doesn't matter?"

201
00:13:05,625 --> 00:13:07,795
I grew up in an orphanage
without any parents.

202
00:13:12,395 --> 00:13:13,735
I'm so ashamed.

203
00:13:14,595 --> 00:13:16,705
You must resent me so much.
I would too, in your shoes.

204
00:13:17,635 --> 00:13:19,065
Look, it's a long story.

205
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:22,945
I heard you studied fashion design.

206
00:13:23,505 --> 00:13:24,645
At Seshin Community College.

207
00:13:24,905 --> 00:13:27,615
I'm so proud. You've turned out so well.

208
00:13:29,115 --> 00:13:30,745
Are you really sure about this?

209
00:13:31,145 --> 00:13:32,715
Of course. I recognized you right away.

210
00:13:33,355 --> 00:13:35,255
You're the spitting image of your mom
in her twenties.

211
00:13:36,055 --> 00:13:38,425
You look a bit like your grandmother, too.
I have a picture of her.

212
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:39,485
I don't want to see it.

213
00:13:44,665 --> 00:13:47,795
From your grandmother's point of view,
she'd only heard one side of the story,

214
00:13:47,865 --> 00:13:51,865
and she doubted if you were really
her son's flesh and blood.

215
00:13:52,205 --> 00:13:55,375
Plus, she had a bad leg. So...

216
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:57,975
If she cared so much,
did she at least write my name on a note?

217
00:13:59,445 --> 00:14:00,445
No.

218
00:14:00,715 --> 00:14:04,345
Anyway, she told me the exact date
and everything.

219
00:14:04,615 --> 00:14:07,315
She made me promise to find you
and make sure.

220
00:14:08,185 --> 00:14:09,625
And you're just now getting to it?

221
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:12,585
Here are your coffees.

222
00:14:17,725 --> 00:14:19,665
Did something happen
that you can't talk about?

223
00:14:20,535 --> 00:14:22,735
No, there's nothing I can't talk about.

224
00:14:23,765 --> 00:14:25,305
Let's get something to eat first.

225
00:14:25,565 --> 00:14:27,475
People get cranky when they're hungry.

226
00:14:28,805 --> 00:14:31,205
- Didn't you have breakfast?
- Isn't it lunchtime?

227
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:33,015
Do you often skip meals?

228
00:14:33,515 --> 00:14:35,945
Don't do that. It's bad for your health.

229
00:14:36,985 --> 00:14:39,715
I saw a restaurant in the lobby
on my way in.

230
00:14:40,815 --> 00:14:42,185
They might not have a table.

231
00:14:42,655 --> 00:14:44,425
If they don't,
we can just eat somewhere else.

232
00:14:51,325 --> 00:14:52,425
Hello.

233
00:14:53,395 --> 00:14:54,435
Thank you.

234
00:15:01,605 --> 00:15:02,705
Where do you live?

235
00:15:03,575 --> 00:15:04,645
In a studio.

236
00:15:05,745 --> 00:15:07,075
No, I mean, which neighborhood?

237
00:15:08,145 --> 00:15:09,175
Hyeonmi-dong.

238
00:15:10,715 --> 00:15:11,985
And you work around here?

239
00:15:13,115 --> 00:15:14,155
In Gangnam.

240
00:15:17,785 --> 00:15:19,025
Do you have a reservation?

241
00:15:19,325 --> 00:15:21,255
- No.
- A table for two?

242
00:15:21,325 --> 00:15:23,995
- Yes.
- Let me check for a table.

243
00:15:26,095 --> 00:15:27,365
Do you have a business card?

244
00:15:34,935 --> 00:15:36,805
(Kim Jin Ju, Staff, Lim Company)

245
00:15:39,675 --> 00:15:40,845
Where do you live?

246
00:15:41,215 --> 00:15:42,215
What?

247
00:15:43,915 --> 00:15:45,145
I need to find a place now.

248
00:15:45,915 --> 00:15:47,255
Did you live abroad?

249
00:15:47,555 --> 00:15:49,155
Right this way.

250
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:50,625
Okay.

251
00:15:57,095 --> 00:15:59,225
I'm afraid all the private rooms
are taken.

252
00:16:04,535 --> 00:16:06,805
Hello? Oh, hello, sir.

253
00:16:29,525 --> 00:16:32,495
Tomorrow? Alright. Thank you.

254
00:16:47,045 --> 00:16:49,915
(Kim Jin Ju, December 3, 1999)

255
00:16:56,785 --> 00:16:59,225
(Kim Jin Ju, December 3, 1999)

256
00:17:06,865 --> 00:17:08,595
Look at CEO Ju, schmoozing.

257
00:17:14,835 --> 00:17:16,745
(Art Folder...)

258
00:17:16,805 --> 00:17:18,545
(Culture Desk 3)

259
00:17:18,605 --> 00:17:19,915
Do you have plans tonight?

260
00:17:20,975 --> 00:17:22,345
- No.
- That's good.

261
00:17:22,615 --> 00:17:24,515
I'm meeting CEO Ju Yeong Ae. Join me.

262
00:17:25,215 --> 00:17:26,215
Is it okay if I come?

263
00:17:26,215 --> 00:17:27,885
You covered her last exhibition,
didn't you?

264
00:17:28,385 --> 00:17:30,385
- But you were the one who...
- French food at the Sun Hotel.

265
00:17:36,895 --> 00:17:38,365
Order whatever you want.

266
00:17:40,295 --> 00:17:42,465
- You have the lunch special, right?
- Yes.

267
00:17:42,535 --> 00:17:44,405
- We'll have that.
- The lunch special for two?

268
00:17:44,465 --> 00:17:45,465
Yes.

269
00:17:48,305 --> 00:17:50,475
Isn't a studio apartment
a little dangerous...

270
00:17:50,845 --> 00:17:51,945
for a woman on her own?

271
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:53,415
It's fine.

272
00:17:54,515 --> 00:17:55,575
What about a boyfriend?

273
00:17:57,115 --> 00:17:58,115
I don't have one.

274
00:18:00,555 --> 00:18:01,815
I'm a man myself,

275
00:18:02,085 --> 00:18:04,325
but there's really no need
to get married these days.

276
00:18:05,185 --> 00:18:07,625
If you do, do it later in life,
after you've done everything you want.

277
00:18:09,225 --> 00:18:13,435
I've learned that life doesn't
always go as planned.

278
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:18,505
I don't know what you'll think of me
for saying this,

279
00:18:19,665 --> 00:18:22,935
but as time went on, I missed you
more and more, and I wondered...

280
00:18:23,305 --> 00:18:26,915
if you'd be tall or short,
or if you took after me at all.

281
00:18:28,345 --> 00:18:31,645
You never left my mind or my heart.

282
00:18:33,755 --> 00:18:36,485
Hwang Mi Sook wouldn't lie
about our child,

283
00:18:36,485 --> 00:18:37,955
and she has no reason to.

284
00:18:39,055 --> 00:18:41,695
For 27 years,
I failed to be a father to you,

285
00:18:42,355 --> 00:18:45,495
so I'll do my best to make up for it
and then some from now on.

286
00:18:48,265 --> 00:18:50,935
Are you managing to save
any of the money you earn?

287
00:19:01,275 --> 00:19:02,815
Let's eat before it gets cold.

288
00:19:14,925 --> 00:19:15,925
This is delicious.

289
00:19:19,865 --> 00:19:21,735
She kept appearing in my dreams
for a while,

290
00:19:22,365 --> 00:19:24,205
and now it's like she's been
reincarnated or something.

291
00:19:26,065 --> 00:19:27,835
Have you ever told her you love her?

292
00:19:28,475 --> 00:19:29,505
To Oiji?

293
00:19:31,175 --> 00:19:32,175
Did I?

294
00:19:33,775 --> 00:19:35,545
Of course I loved her.

295
00:19:38,285 --> 00:19:39,915
You know, Ba Ra likes puppies too.

296
00:19:42,885 --> 00:19:44,785
I wonder if she'd accept
a puppy as a gift.

297
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:47,095
Ms. Noh Hye Yeong said she was
running 30 minutes late.

298
00:19:47,295 --> 00:19:49,865
That woman has no sense of time.

299
00:19:51,165 --> 00:19:52,465
Is Jin Ju out on set?

300
00:19:52,795 --> 00:19:53,895
It's her day off today.

301
00:19:58,805 --> 00:19:59,805
It's uncanny.

302
00:20:00,435 --> 00:20:02,275
It's like I'm sitting here
with Hwang Mi Sook.

303
00:20:04,545 --> 00:20:06,005
What did she do for a living?

304
00:20:06,505 --> 00:20:07,515
A nurse.

305
00:20:09,985 --> 00:20:11,085
At what hospital?

306
00:20:12,915 --> 00:20:15,985
I found out she got married and emigrated.

307
00:20:24,065 --> 00:20:25,695
If you're anything like me,

308
00:20:26,365 --> 00:20:27,935
you're probably a very honest person.

309
00:20:28,565 --> 00:20:30,465
I don't hide things or deceive people.

310
00:20:32,265 --> 00:20:35,475
You'll find out eventually anyway.
I was away at "school" all this time.

311
00:20:36,005 --> 00:20:37,145
You know what I mean by "school," right?

312
00:20:38,405 --> 00:20:39,405
Prison.

313
00:20:41,045 --> 00:20:44,615
That's why I couldn't look for you,
even though I desperately wanted to.

314
00:20:45,185 --> 00:20:48,485
I got tangled up in some things,
and parts of it were unfair,

315
00:20:50,325 --> 00:20:51,885
but I just see it all as fate.

316
00:20:54,325 --> 00:20:56,195
For that long?

317
00:20:56,595 --> 00:20:58,695
I got out on parole eight years ago.

318
00:21:00,935 --> 00:21:02,665
But you went back in?

319
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:07,705
From now on, I'm going to live for you,
and only for you.

320
00:21:08,175 --> 00:21:10,445
That's why I came looking for you
with so much confidence.

321
00:21:15,145 --> 00:21:16,175
Are you disappointed?

322
00:21:16,515 --> 00:21:18,115
Were you hoping for some big-shot parents?

323
00:21:19,845 --> 00:21:23,385
The past is in the past.
You have to live for the future.

324
00:21:23,855 --> 00:21:26,085
There's no moving forward
if you're stuck in the past.

325
00:21:26,585 --> 00:21:28,525
You're not alone in the world anymore.

326
00:21:28,895 --> 00:21:31,825
You have a dad you can count on,
so hold your head high.

327
00:21:33,095 --> 00:21:37,365
If you have even the slightest doubt,
we can get a test tomorrow to be sure.

328
00:21:38,235 --> 00:21:39,235
No.

329
00:21:41,235 --> 00:21:44,845
There were only two babies left there
on December 21, 1999.

330
00:21:45,305 --> 00:21:47,015
Geum Ba Ra doesn't look anything like me.

331
00:21:47,315 --> 00:21:49,515
You just know
when it's your own flesh and blood.

332
00:21:51,585 --> 00:21:53,515
Is there anything you're curious about,

333
00:21:53,785 --> 00:21:54,985
or anything you wish for?

334
00:21:58,025 --> 00:21:59,225
I'll have to think about it.

335
00:22:01,095 --> 00:22:02,225
Why aren't you eating?

336
00:22:03,565 --> 00:22:05,765
- I'm full.
- Are you on a diet?

337
00:22:06,665 --> 00:22:08,065
I just don't have much of an appetite.

338
00:22:18,775 --> 00:22:21,775
So, family shouldn't live apart, right?

339
00:22:22,075 --> 00:22:23,685
We need to save money on rent.

340
00:22:24,345 --> 00:22:27,155
I don't have much stuff anyway.
I could move in tomorrow.

341
00:22:28,085 --> 00:22:30,185
- To my place?
- Yes.

342
00:22:30,755 --> 00:22:32,555
- Why?
- What do you mean, "why?"

343
00:22:32,625 --> 00:22:33,995
Aren't we family?

344
00:22:35,495 --> 00:22:37,665
It's a studio apartment. Just one room.

345
00:22:38,565 --> 00:22:39,865
I know it's a studio.

346
00:22:40,335 --> 00:22:41,865
It has a living room and kitchen area,
doesn't it?

347
00:22:42,365 --> 00:22:45,135
I can just sleep in a corner.
I just need a sleeping bag.

348
00:22:54,815 --> 00:22:56,845
- Hello.
- Hello.

349
00:23:01,585 --> 00:23:02,655
What about Kim Jeong Ah?

350
00:23:02,715 --> 00:23:04,355
She had to kill a story
at the last minute.

351
00:23:04,355 --> 00:23:05,385
I see.

352
00:23:05,385 --> 00:23:07,225
A journalist I’m close with once said,

353
00:23:07,825 --> 00:23:11,095
"Being a reporter would be a great job
if you didn't have to write stories."

354
00:23:11,725 --> 00:23:12,725
That's what she said.

355
00:23:13,195 --> 00:23:14,195
Right.

356
00:23:23,005 --> 00:23:24,005
Hello.

357
00:23:25,875 --> 00:23:26,875
A pleasure to meet you.

358
00:23:30,585 --> 00:23:33,185
Our reporter, Kim Jeong Ah,
had to kill a story at the last minute.

359
00:23:33,615 --> 00:23:36,085
- So I'm here instead.
- Well, not "instead."

360
00:23:36,755 --> 00:23:38,455
Your exhibition article was so great,

361
00:23:38,585 --> 00:23:41,295
I've been meaning to set something up.

362
00:23:41,425 --> 00:23:43,195
There was so much great work
to write about.

363
00:23:43,665 --> 00:23:45,365
How long did it take to prepare?

364
00:23:45,565 --> 00:23:46,765
Almost a year.

365
00:23:48,165 --> 00:23:52,005
Ma'am, the hospital just called.
She's suddenly taken a turn for the worse.

366
00:23:54,805 --> 00:23:57,775
My mother-in-law is in the ICU.

367
00:23:58,245 --> 00:24:01,045
- You should go right away.
- I'm so sorry about this.

368
00:24:01,175 --> 00:24:02,215
Which hospital?

369
00:24:05,115 --> 00:24:07,915
- Korea Sam Hospital.
- But traffic is terrible right now.

370
00:24:08,155 --> 00:24:10,985
- I'll take care of the bill later...
- No, please don't worry about it.

371
00:24:11,625 --> 00:24:13,255
- Go on.
- No, really.

372
00:24:14,325 --> 00:24:17,025
Well, I'll make it up to you next time.
Please, don't get up.

373
00:24:17,325 --> 00:24:18,365
You too.

374
00:24:26,535 --> 00:24:29,175
Oh, Father

375
00:24:31,375 --> 00:24:34,175
Oh, Father

376
00:24:36,575 --> 00:24:41,355
Our prayers

377
00:24:43,115 --> 00:24:45,825
Please, answer them

378
00:24:51,795 --> 00:24:52,795
Answer them?

379
00:24:52,795 --> 00:24:54,435
(Answer them?)

380
00:24:54,595 --> 00:24:55,595
My foot.

381
00:24:55,665 --> 00:24:58,435
(My foot.)

382
00:25:03,435 --> 00:25:06,205
I've never met an artist based in Germany.

383
00:25:06,205 --> 00:25:07,775
How did you end up there?

384
00:25:07,845 --> 00:25:09,075
This isn't an interview, by the way.

385
00:25:09,545 --> 00:25:12,185
My closest friend
from my high school class...

386
00:25:12,515 --> 00:25:13,815
went to study abroad in Germany.

387
00:25:14,115 --> 00:25:15,555
So you followed your friend to Germany?

388
00:25:16,185 --> 00:25:17,185
You could say that.

389
00:25:17,255 --> 00:25:20,555
When you live there a long time,
do you start to become like the locals?

390
00:25:21,125 --> 00:25:24,765
Do I seem a bit stiff?
I get that sometimes.

391
00:25:25,125 --> 00:25:29,835
You definitely have a different vibe
from most Korean men your age.

392
00:25:31,805 --> 00:25:33,235
I'm a Korean man too.

393
00:25:34,505 --> 00:25:36,375
I just had to change my citizenship,
that's all.

394
00:25:37,675 --> 00:25:40,075
You're not much of a talker, are you?

395
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:42,815
This is our second time meeting,
and that's the sense I'm getting.

396
00:25:43,045 --> 00:25:44,815
I'll make an exception today.

397
00:25:46,745 --> 00:25:49,585
How do you feel about
the positive reaction...

398
00:25:50,015 --> 00:25:51,155
your work has been getting in Korea?

399
00:25:52,255 --> 00:25:55,025
Sorry. That came out sounding
like an interview question.

400
00:25:55,095 --> 00:25:57,965
When my hard work is seen and appreciated,

401
00:25:58,225 --> 00:25:59,295
it feels good, of course.

402
00:26:00,195 --> 00:26:02,095
I think people are drawn to the affection
in my work.

403
00:26:02,165 --> 00:26:04,905
Is that the main theme?

404
00:26:05,105 --> 00:26:06,105
Isn't it?

405
00:26:08,605 --> 00:26:11,775
How many years were you in Germany?
It seems like it's been over 20.

406
00:26:12,105 --> 00:26:14,315
Yes, a full 26 years.

407
00:26:14,675 --> 00:26:16,475
But your Korean is perfect.

408
00:26:16,775 --> 00:26:19,715
- Is your best friend still there...
- No.

409
00:26:20,015 --> 00:26:21,585
I never even got to meet him there.

410
00:26:22,715 --> 00:26:24,755
I was in an accident
the day after I arrived.

411
00:26:25,425 --> 00:26:27,325
My gosh, what kind of accident?

412
00:26:27,625 --> 00:26:28,655
A car accident.

413
00:26:29,725 --> 00:26:32,995
I had a pretty bad head injury,
so I was unconscious for a while.

414
00:26:33,365 --> 00:26:35,195
And even after I woke up,
I was in and out of it for a few years.

415
00:26:35,595 --> 00:26:38,105
- Oh, dear.
- So I never had the chance to find him.

416
00:26:39,805 --> 00:26:41,835
I actually met up with him
when I came back to Korea this time.

417
00:26:42,305 --> 00:26:44,245
Turns out he's a managing director
at Jeil Auto.

418
00:26:44,375 --> 00:26:45,775
You must have been so happy to see him.

419
00:26:46,475 --> 00:26:47,475
Yes.

420
00:26:47,475 --> 00:26:49,875
After almost three decades,

421
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:51,885
Korea's changed a lot, hasn't it?

422
00:26:53,085 --> 00:26:55,615
- Yes.
- How many times did you return?

423
00:26:55,885 --> 00:26:58,125
Just once, 11 years ago...

424
00:26:59,985 --> 00:27:01,595
It was when my mother passed away.

425
00:27:02,725 --> 00:27:04,565
I couldn't be there when my father passed.

426
00:27:05,625 --> 00:27:07,795
You must have gone through a lot
in Germany.

427
00:27:08,065 --> 00:27:10,035
But it turned out to be
a lucky break, in a way.

428
00:27:10,605 --> 00:27:12,665
The person who caused my accident
passed away last year.

429
00:27:13,535 --> 00:27:14,635
He was my adoptive father.

430
00:27:14,975 --> 00:27:17,875
- Oh my.
- He must have felt so guilty about it,

431
00:27:19,175 --> 00:27:22,315
though he always said it was
because he recognized my talent.

432
00:27:22,715 --> 00:27:23,985
He adopted me as his son.

433
00:27:26,945 --> 00:27:28,685
Thanks to him,
my language skills improved quickly,

434
00:27:29,215 --> 00:27:32,525
and he was a famous painter and professor,
Ilias Becker.

435
00:27:33,055 --> 00:27:34,255
You can look him up.

436
00:27:34,795 --> 00:27:36,695
He truly saved my life.

437
00:27:38,065 --> 00:27:39,865
So that's how you got your citizenship.

438
00:27:40,125 --> 00:27:42,795
I just assumed
you had married a German woman.

439
00:27:44,065 --> 00:27:45,335
A blessing in disguise, isn't it?

440
00:27:45,805 --> 00:27:47,705
To think that an unfortunate accident
led to...

441
00:27:47,835 --> 00:27:50,905
Yes. You win some, and you lose some.

442
00:27:51,075 --> 00:27:53,145
And misfortune can turn into good luck.

443
00:27:53,205 --> 00:27:55,615
You must believe that
someone up there was looking out for you.

444
00:27:55,775 --> 00:27:58,485
I believe that the skies help
those who help themselves.

445
00:27:59,245 --> 00:28:03,725
As my father's assistant and secretary,
studying and working on my art,

446
00:28:04,885 --> 00:28:07,695
I don't think
I had a single second to spare.

447
00:28:08,325 --> 00:28:09,425
That's incredible.

448
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:13,025
Are you okay now, health-wise?
Are there any lingering effects?

449
00:28:13,125 --> 00:28:14,235
I recovered fully.

450
00:28:14,495 --> 00:28:16,535
I even slept less
to make time to exercise.

451
00:28:17,605 --> 00:28:21,475
Listening to you makes me realize
how much further I have to go.

452
00:28:21,835 --> 00:28:24,605
You made it as a reporter
for Sungwoo Daily by giving it your all.

453
00:28:25,405 --> 00:28:26,605
They don't just hand you that job,
do they?

454
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:31,615
- Mr. Kim. I mean, sir.
- Call me what you're comfortable with.

455
00:28:34,355 --> 00:28:35,915
Thinking about Korea now
versus when you left,

456
00:28:36,185 --> 00:28:39,225
is there anything that's changed
in a way you don't like?

457
00:28:39,625 --> 00:28:41,695
When do you feel out of place?

458
00:28:42,925 --> 00:28:44,225
I'm asking a lot of questions, aren't I?

459
00:28:44,565 --> 00:28:45,795
There's just so much I'm curious about.

460
00:28:46,125 --> 00:28:47,395
No, this is what
we're supposed to talk about.

461
00:28:48,465 --> 00:28:49,995
Otherwise,
we'd just be staring at each other.

462
00:28:51,205 --> 00:28:53,065
One thing that throws me off sometimes...

463
00:28:53,505 --> 00:28:55,875
Maybe it's because I'm used to
the German way of thinking,

464
00:28:56,475 --> 00:28:59,875
but it's when people just hit you
with personal questions out of nowhere.

465
00:29:01,315 --> 00:29:04,315
Like, "Why aren't you married?"
or "Have you ever dated a German woman?"

466
00:29:04,415 --> 00:29:05,945
Or, "Let me set you up with someone."

467
00:29:05,945 --> 00:29:07,015
Yes.

468
00:29:07,185 --> 00:29:09,385
That's just our way of showing we care.

469
00:29:10,115 --> 00:29:13,855
But we should focus that energy
on ourselves.

470
00:29:14,255 --> 00:29:15,295
Excuse me.

471
00:29:15,495 --> 00:29:17,695
Of all the photos taken of me in Korea,

472
00:29:18,695 --> 00:29:19,865
this is my favorite.

473
00:29:30,645 --> 00:29:31,805
(Yong Joong)

474
00:29:36,575 --> 00:29:37,685
It's been a while.

475
00:29:38,015 --> 00:29:39,185
Do I always have to call first?

476
00:29:39,645 --> 00:29:41,515
I could tell you were busy.

477
00:29:42,215 --> 00:29:45,185
Did you bug my place?
You've never even been to my house.

478
00:29:45,385 --> 00:29:47,295
I just close my eyes,
and I can see everything.

479
00:29:47,695 --> 00:29:50,295
Seeing whoever I thought about
would be a great power.

480
00:29:52,725 --> 00:29:53,795
Momo?

481
00:29:54,765 --> 00:29:55,765
No, you.

482
00:29:58,635 --> 00:29:59,665
You're home, right?

483
00:30:00,005 --> 00:30:01,005
Yes.

484
00:30:01,505 --> 00:30:05,445
Come to think of it,
you've never invited me over.

485
00:30:05,505 --> 00:30:08,075
That's why I'm calling.
I want to invite you over today.

486
00:30:09,845 --> 00:30:12,515
- How long will that take?
- You're here?

487
00:30:12,685 --> 00:30:14,815
- Yes.
- Oh my gosh.

488
00:30:14,885 --> 00:30:17,155
Don't worry about dressing up.
Just come as you are.

489
00:30:17,855 --> 00:30:18,855
One minute.

490
00:30:38,445 --> 00:30:40,145
When did you get so pretty?

491
00:30:40,615 --> 00:30:41,845
I've always been pretty.

492
00:30:51,225 --> 00:30:53,755
- Are we really going to your place?
- Yes.

493
00:30:54,325 --> 00:30:56,825
Then I should get you something.
It's my first visit.

494
00:30:57,295 --> 00:30:58,965
- Did you have lunch?
- Of course.

495
00:30:59,265 --> 00:31:01,535
- You haven't yet?
- It's not that I didn't eat, I couldn't.

496
00:31:01,535 --> 00:31:02,795
I was swamped.

497
00:31:03,295 --> 00:31:04,505
You're always busy.

498
00:31:05,165 --> 00:31:06,235
It's already 4 p.m.

499
00:31:07,035 --> 00:31:10,075
Have you fallen out of love with me?
I won't expect a phone call.

500
00:31:10,135 --> 00:31:11,745
But you could send a text at least.

501
00:31:12,505 --> 00:31:13,915
You're the one who acts busy.

502
00:31:14,375 --> 00:31:16,375
Don't you dare turn this around on me.

503
00:31:17,585 --> 00:31:20,785
- You don't eat street food, do you?
- Why wouldn't I?

504
00:31:21,185 --> 00:31:24,125
It's too early for dinner,
so how about some tteokbokki? Okay?

505
00:31:25,025 --> 00:31:26,025
Okay.

506
00:31:26,025 --> 00:31:27,955
Here you are. Enjoy.

507
00:31:28,025 --> 00:31:29,395
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

508
00:31:35,535 --> 00:31:38,965
Tteokbokki was the very first thing I made
the day I moved out on my own.

509
00:31:40,065 --> 00:31:41,575
I'll never forget that day.

510
00:31:42,435 --> 00:31:44,705
What was the best part
of being on your own?

511
00:31:47,345 --> 00:31:50,215
Having my very own space
for the first time in my life.

512
00:31:50,685 --> 00:31:52,185
A real home, not an institution.

513
00:31:52,385 --> 00:31:55,085
It was so quiet at night,
with no one snoring,

514
00:31:55,155 --> 00:31:57,585
that I couldn't sleep
because I was so happy.

515
00:31:57,655 --> 00:31:58,955
Girls snore?

516
00:31:59,025 --> 00:32:00,895
When they're tired,
it's so loud it shakes walls.

517
00:32:01,225 --> 00:32:02,525
You probably snore too, right?

518
00:32:02,895 --> 00:32:05,295
I don't think so.
No one's ever told me I do.

519
00:32:05,695 --> 00:32:08,365
My brother says
I'm a pretty quiet sleeper for a guy.

520
00:32:10,495 --> 00:32:11,965
Have you seen my brother recently?

521
00:32:12,935 --> 00:32:13,935
No.

522
00:32:15,405 --> 00:32:16,575
Listen, just in case...

523
00:32:18,405 --> 00:32:19,405
What?

524
00:32:20,175 --> 00:32:23,315
Now that my brother is getting older,
he can sometimes go overboard.

525
00:32:23,575 --> 00:32:25,845
If he does, try to be understanding.
He's my brother, after all.

526
00:32:26,515 --> 00:32:27,785
Go overboard how?

527
00:32:28,255 --> 00:32:30,825
He's just different from me in some ways.

528
00:32:42,595 --> 00:32:46,235
Sir. I just got a call
that Lee Eun Hye came to the office today.

529
00:32:46,305 --> 00:32:48,505
A man claiming to be
Kim Jin Ju's father came...

530
00:32:48,505 --> 00:32:49,905
and is demanding her address.

531
00:32:49,975 --> 00:32:51,575
He says he hasn't been able to reach her
for ten days.

532
00:32:51,845 --> 00:32:53,945
What are you talking about? What father?

533
00:32:53,945 --> 00:32:55,475
That's what I mean.

534
00:32:55,915 --> 00:32:57,045
Tell him she quit.

535
00:32:57,115 --> 00:32:58,885
We did, but he still demands her address.

536
00:32:59,215 --> 00:33:01,055
He says he knows she's in Hyeonmi-dong.

537
00:33:02,115 --> 00:33:05,755
What should I do?
He's not leaving until we give it to him.

538
00:33:06,185 --> 00:33:07,795
Tell Eun Hye to call me.

539
00:33:12,495 --> 00:33:15,965
Hello.
I'm Kim Gwang Cheol, Jin Ju's father.

540
00:33:16,495 --> 00:33:17,505
I see.

541
00:33:18,065 --> 00:33:19,205
Are you the CEO?

542
00:33:19,805 --> 00:33:21,005
I am. What is this about?

543
00:33:22,775 --> 00:33:26,475
On the 14th, I met my daughter, Jin Ju,
at the Joongang Hotel.

544
00:33:27,245 --> 00:33:28,315
Did you hear about that?

545
00:33:28,945 --> 00:33:29,975
No.

546
00:33:30,275 --> 00:33:33,185
We even ate at the hotel's Japanese spot
before parting ways.

547
00:33:33,515 --> 00:33:35,915
But four days later, I couldn't reach her.

548
00:33:36,255 --> 00:33:38,055
Her phone's been off ever since.

549
00:33:38,985 --> 00:33:40,655
She quit almost a week ago.

550
00:33:40,925 --> 00:33:42,995
Did she say she found another job?

551
00:33:43,625 --> 00:33:46,265
I asked, but she said
she just wanted to take a break.

552
00:33:46,565 --> 00:33:48,735
If she'd gotten another job,
I would've heard about it right away.

553
00:33:48,795 --> 00:33:50,295
I have to go find her.

554
00:33:50,635 --> 00:33:53,405
If you don't trust me, send someone along.

555
00:33:54,175 --> 00:33:56,475
I only know that she lives
in Hyeonmi-dong.

556
00:33:57,375 --> 00:33:59,145
Please give me her address.

557
00:34:01,445 --> 00:34:03,475
You never know,
something could've happened to her.

558
00:34:04,315 --> 00:34:05,315
She might have gone on a trip...

559
00:34:05,385 --> 00:34:07,585
Will you take responsibility
if something happened?

560
00:34:09,985 --> 00:34:11,585
Let me speak to my employee.

561
00:34:16,055 --> 00:34:17,055
Hello?

562
00:34:17,595 --> 00:34:19,995
- Yes?
- Are any of the men working today?

563
00:34:20,165 --> 00:34:21,195
Hwang Jae Young.

564
00:34:22,995 --> 00:34:24,665
You didn't eat on purpose, did you?

565
00:34:24,865 --> 00:34:26,965
Not at all. I really enjoyed it.

566
00:34:27,265 --> 00:34:28,805
I've been craving
the tteokbokki from here.

567
00:34:28,805 --> 00:34:29,805
(CEO James Ha)

568
00:34:31,005 --> 00:34:32,505
- It's Mr. Ha.
- I'll get it.

569
00:34:34,845 --> 00:34:37,045
What's up? I'm here with Ba Ra.

570
00:34:37,115 --> 00:34:38,315
Good. Put her on.

571
00:34:38,685 --> 00:34:40,815
- Why?
- I need to ask her something.

572
00:34:40,815 --> 00:34:43,655
A man came by
claiming to be Kim Jin Ju's birth father.

573
00:34:45,455 --> 00:34:46,985
Did Kim Jin Ju meet her birth father?

574
00:34:49,325 --> 00:34:51,325
- Hello?
- It's James.

575
00:34:51,665 --> 00:34:55,195
- Hello, sir.
- Please, drop the "sir."

576
00:34:55,995 --> 00:34:58,965
Did you happen to hear that
Kim Jin Ju met her birth father?

577
00:35:01,535 --> 00:35:04,605
- Yes.
- And you haven't spoken to her recently?

578
00:35:05,545 --> 00:35:07,715
No, it's been a while.

579
00:35:08,275 --> 00:35:09,845
What about quitting her job with us?

580
00:35:10,615 --> 00:35:11,945
She quit?

581
00:35:13,485 --> 00:35:15,555
The phone is turned off.

582
00:35:15,615 --> 00:35:18,525
Please leave a message after the tone.

583
00:35:18,525 --> 00:35:19,885
Charges will apply...

584
00:35:25,095 --> 00:35:26,825
What was the man
who claimed to be her father like?

585
00:35:27,365 --> 00:35:30,295
He was pretty well-dressed.

586
00:35:31,205 --> 00:35:32,405
What does he do for a living?

587
00:35:32,965 --> 00:35:34,205
I didn't get into that.

588
00:35:34,705 --> 00:35:36,505
He said right away that I wasn't her.

589
00:35:37,375 --> 00:35:39,745
At least she met her biological father,
right?

590
00:35:41,815 --> 00:35:43,275
We're making one stop first.

591
00:35:44,485 --> 00:35:45,485
Where?

592
00:35:48,015 --> 00:35:49,855
Can't you tell me? I'm curious.

593
00:35:50,555 --> 00:35:51,585
A pet shop.

594
00:35:52,625 --> 00:35:54,525
- I can't get a pet.
- Yes, you can.

595
00:35:54,525 --> 00:35:55,755
I can't just leave it at home alone.

596
00:35:55,825 --> 00:35:57,125
I've already thought about all that.

597
00:36:09,005 --> 00:36:12,175
Then, instead of buying one,
let's go to an animal shelter.

598
00:36:13,105 --> 00:36:16,875
If I were in a position to have one,
I was thinking of adopting a rescue.

599
00:36:17,075 --> 00:36:18,115
Okay?

600
00:36:18,215 --> 00:36:20,345
Think it through so you have no regrets.

601
00:36:20,445 --> 00:36:22,615
I won't. I've even volunteered there.

602
00:36:24,625 --> 00:36:25,985
Yong Joong.

603
00:36:27,285 --> 00:36:28,295
The address.

604
00:37:17,205 --> 00:37:21,545
I don't know who'll be the first
to read this,

605
00:37:21,845 --> 00:37:23,345
but by that time, I'll probably be...

606
00:37:27,985 --> 00:37:31,955
with the grandmother I never got to meet.

607
00:37:32,225 --> 00:37:33,855
I'm so exhausted,

608
00:37:34,595 --> 00:37:36,955
and my last glimmer of hope is gone.

609
00:37:37,555 --> 00:37:40,065
I wonder what my real parents are like.

610
00:37:41,165 --> 00:37:43,695
I would dream and imagine,

611
00:37:43,865 --> 00:37:46,265
and that's what gave me hope.

612
00:37:47,465 --> 00:37:49,235
That's how I kept going.

613
00:37:49,835 --> 00:37:51,645
But that hope was shattered.

614
00:37:52,745 --> 00:37:54,315
Mr. James,

615
00:37:55,145 --> 00:37:58,945
I'm sorry, and thank you for everything
you've done for me.

616
00:38:00,185 --> 00:38:03,055
Momo, while we worked together,

617
00:38:03,555 --> 00:38:07,255
I had so much fun
and really developed an eye for things.

618
00:38:07,795 --> 00:38:08,825
Thank you.

619
00:38:09,395 --> 00:38:10,895
We have to report this to the police,
right?

620
00:38:13,425 --> 00:38:14,765
Oh my gosh!

621
00:38:15,895 --> 00:38:18,335
What is going on now? Seriously.

622
00:38:29,615 --> 00:38:31,745
I like big dogs,

623
00:38:31,945 --> 00:38:33,245
but in an apartment...

624
00:38:33,385 --> 00:38:34,555
Don't worry about it.

625
00:38:35,015 --> 00:38:36,085
Choose from one of these.

626
00:38:37,825 --> 00:38:38,825
(James)

627
00:38:53,765 --> 00:38:55,105
Is Reporter Geum with you?

628
00:38:55,505 --> 00:38:57,905
No, it was loud,
so I stepped out to take the call.

629
00:38:57,975 --> 00:39:01,715
Kim Jin Ju, Ba Ra's orphanage friend,
disappeared, possibly to take her life.

630
00:39:03,845 --> 00:39:04,845
Are you serious?

631
00:39:05,145 --> 00:39:06,245
Yes.

632
00:39:07,215 --> 00:39:09,355
- Why?
- I don't know the details,

633
00:39:09,355 --> 00:39:11,955
but Reporter Geum
is going to be devastated. This is awful.

634
00:39:12,025 --> 00:39:15,595
What do we do?
I heard they grew up like sisters.

635
00:39:15,955 --> 00:39:16,955
Are you sure about this?

636
00:39:17,025 --> 00:39:19,025
Her father and a staff member of mine
went to her home,

637
00:39:19,025 --> 00:39:20,765
and they found a letter she'd left behind.

638
00:39:46,355 --> 00:39:47,895
Just when I finally met her.

639
00:39:49,725 --> 00:39:51,925
After everything I went through
to find her.

640
00:40:02,375 --> 00:40:03,435
Ba Ra.

641
00:40:04,235 --> 00:40:06,305
Even if I didn't always show it,

642
00:40:06,975 --> 00:40:09,315
and if there were ever times I hurt you,

643
00:40:10,515 --> 00:40:12,615
because we were like sisters,

644
00:40:13,615 --> 00:40:15,215
please just remember the good times.

645
00:40:16,785 --> 00:40:20,155
Having you with me
really made it less lonely.

646
00:40:20,755 --> 00:40:22,025
You were such a big support for me.

647
00:40:23,855 --> 00:40:28,795
When I think about it,
I must have been happiest in the womb.

648
00:40:29,435 --> 00:40:30,995
They say even fetuses can feel things,
you know.

649
00:40:32,105 --> 00:40:34,235
You know I've always loved water, right?

650
00:40:34,805 --> 00:40:37,735
I'm going to find my peace in the water.

651
00:40:39,175 --> 00:40:41,845
I thought we would be
like a family forever.

652
00:40:43,815 --> 00:40:45,385
A wave of sadness is washing over me.

653
00:41:03,795 --> 00:41:05,135
Jin Ju, eat up.

654
00:41:05,565 --> 00:41:07,805
- I heard your grades went up.
- Yes, they did.

655
00:41:09,075 --> 00:41:10,205
Eat up.

656
00:41:12,875 --> 00:41:14,205
Eat up.

657
00:41:19,385 --> 00:41:20,985
Hey, did you get a banana?

658
00:41:21,555 --> 00:41:22,555
Yes.

659
00:41:25,385 --> 00:41:28,995
If you get adopted,
that lady won't volunteer anymore, right?

660
00:41:29,055 --> 00:41:31,865
She said she'd keep coming.
She finds it rewarding.

661
00:41:31,925 --> 00:41:33,525
Will you come back and visit?

662
00:41:34,365 --> 00:41:37,235
- I'm going to miss you.
- Me too.

663
00:41:38,105 --> 00:41:40,965
I can't come weekly because of school,
but I'll visit as often as I can.

664
00:41:43,375 --> 00:41:47,345
Everything should be finalized
by next week.

665
00:41:47,805 --> 00:41:48,875
Thank you.

666
00:41:49,175 --> 00:41:50,775
You've worked so hard for us.

667
00:41:50,975 --> 00:41:53,915
To be honest, our foundation's chairman...

668
00:41:54,045 --> 00:41:56,655
really doted on Ba Ra
and thinks the world of her.

669
00:41:56,655 --> 00:41:58,525
It's not that he was against it,

670
00:41:58,855 --> 00:42:00,355
but he wasn't exactly thrilled about it.

671
00:42:01,055 --> 00:42:04,565
He kept asking why it had to be her,
saying she's the face of the orphanage.

672
00:42:04,665 --> 00:42:07,025
It's impossible not to love Ba Ra.

673
00:42:07,165 --> 00:42:09,235
She's so kind and hardworking.

674
00:42:10,235 --> 00:42:11,235
Excuse me.

675
00:42:14,505 --> 00:42:15,535
What?

676
00:42:15,735 --> 00:42:17,505
Did you lose something?

677
00:42:18,375 --> 00:42:21,105
- My wallet...
- Your wallet is missing?

678
00:42:22,445 --> 00:42:25,615
Hello? Hi, honey.
I'll call you right back.

679
00:42:28,215 --> 00:42:29,485
Everyone, down to the auditorium.

680
00:42:29,485 --> 00:42:31,885
Deok Young, go and get
Mi Su and Seon Uk. Quickly.

681
00:42:31,955 --> 00:42:32,955
Okay.

682
00:42:46,535 --> 00:42:48,575
Don't just glance around.
Search everywhere!

683
00:42:49,075 --> 00:42:50,105
We have to find it.

684
00:42:53,705 --> 00:42:54,715
(Kim Jin Ju)

685
00:43:01,145 --> 00:43:02,155
Is this...

686
00:43:02,555 --> 00:43:03,555
Thank you.

687
00:43:08,395 --> 00:43:10,655
Is anything missing?

688
00:43:12,265 --> 00:43:14,765
There was 500 dollars in cash.

689
00:43:16,195 --> 00:43:19,235
I'm positive I put exactly 500 dollars
in here.

690
00:43:19,535 --> 00:43:20,865
All in new bills...

691
00:43:21,705 --> 00:43:23,375
I was going to give it to the kids
for their allowance.

692
00:43:24,305 --> 00:43:25,305
(Geum Ba Ra)

693
00:43:48,165 --> 00:43:49,635
Why would I do that?

694
00:43:50,565 --> 00:43:52,465
I have no reason to.

695
00:43:59,505 --> 00:44:00,505
Go to your room.

696
00:44:02,275 --> 00:44:03,275
Didn't you hear me?

697
00:44:17,855 --> 00:44:20,495
(Unpo Police Station)

698
00:44:21,765 --> 00:44:23,935
Her phone's last signal was
at Yeongdeung Port.

699
00:44:24,435 --> 00:44:26,335
And we've seen no signs of activity since.

700
00:44:26,865 --> 00:44:28,335
Considering she left a note,
it's pretty clear.

701
00:44:29,735 --> 00:44:30,735
But you can't be sure.

702
00:44:31,135 --> 00:44:32,305
She might've faked it
to escape her father.

703
00:44:32,575 --> 00:44:34,575
Then she would've at least taken money
or her credit cards.

704
00:44:35,145 --> 00:44:36,875
Her bank accounts and debit card
are untouched.

705
00:44:37,415 --> 00:44:38,945
I'm telling you,
there's no sign of activity.

706
00:44:40,485 --> 00:44:43,215
- We have Kim Jin Ju on CCTV.
- Where?

707
00:44:43,215 --> 00:44:44,485
A convenience store at Yeongdeung Port.

708
00:44:53,995 --> 00:44:55,335
Does this make any sense to you, Ba Ra?

709
00:44:55,595 --> 00:44:57,035
I can't believe it either.

710
00:44:57,535 --> 00:44:59,035
Is she that fragile?

711
00:44:59,865 --> 00:45:02,675
- She must be somewhere...
- This might be out of line,

712
00:45:03,105 --> 00:45:04,505
but have you considered that...

713
00:45:05,105 --> 00:45:07,545
she might not be your biological daughter,
although the facts might line up?

714
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:16,385
I already had it checked, just in case.

715
00:45:16,755 --> 00:45:18,855
I got a hold of her toothbrush
and some hair.

716
00:45:22,795 --> 00:45:25,765
(DNA analysis report)

717
00:45:27,965 --> 00:45:29,765
(Test result details)

718
00:45:29,835 --> 00:45:32,305
(Genetic match test results:
99.99 percent paternity match verified)

719
00:45:32,365 --> 00:45:35,075
(Paternity between Kim Gwang Cheol
and Kim Jin Ju is confirmed)

720
00:45:37,075 --> 00:45:41,475
I didn't even know she existed,
and this is how she twists the knife?

721
00:45:42,945 --> 00:45:44,515
I need Momo's number.

722
00:45:45,245 --> 00:45:47,945
Someone like Momo
could easily be hiding her.

723
00:45:49,955 --> 00:45:52,155
Momo just had a death in her family, too.

724
00:45:52,555 --> 00:45:54,485
She has neither the time
nor the reason to do that.

725
00:45:55,725 --> 00:45:57,195
What are you, her spokesperson?

726
00:45:59,025 --> 00:46:00,025
Whatever.

727
00:46:01,865 --> 00:46:04,335
- I only have her agency's number.
- And you're a reporter?

728
00:46:04,735 --> 00:46:07,565
You have no idea how strict
celebrity agencies are in Korea.

729
00:46:09,875 --> 00:46:11,505
Especially with reporters.

730
00:46:12,445 --> 00:46:14,475
No matter what her biological father
was like,

731
00:46:15,045 --> 00:46:18,715
how could she just throw her life away?
That has to be the only reason.

732
00:46:18,845 --> 00:46:20,245
She must have been
incredibly disappointed.

733
00:46:21,015 --> 00:46:22,415
Especially since she saw
the ankle bracelet.

734
00:46:23,085 --> 00:46:24,855
I'd be horrified too, if I were her.

735
00:46:25,625 --> 00:46:27,355
Especially with some man
who's claiming to be your father.

736
00:46:28,625 --> 00:46:30,425
- Manager Yoon.
- Yes?

737
00:46:30,425 --> 00:46:34,395
Let's live a long, full life.
No matter what hardships we face.

738
00:46:34,895 --> 00:46:35,895
Right.

739
00:46:39,235 --> 00:46:40,235
You don't think...

740
00:46:43,005 --> 00:46:44,775
Do you think she might have
gone to Momo's?

741
00:46:45,445 --> 00:46:48,445
- No way.
- But Jin Ju was so good to Momo.

742
00:46:48,975 --> 00:46:51,315
Even though Jin Ju's the older one,
she catered to her every whim.

743
00:46:52,045 --> 00:46:54,145
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

744
00:46:55,155 --> 00:46:56,255
You haven't heard from her, have you?

745
00:46:57,315 --> 00:46:58,955
I haven't spoken to her in ages.

746
00:47:00,425 --> 00:47:01,425
Okay, got it.

747
00:47:03,055 --> 00:47:04,325
Are you going to stay there?

748
00:47:04,595 --> 00:47:06,965
I hurt my back a little.
It's a long story.

749
00:47:07,595 --> 00:47:09,265
Besides, she probably just
went off the grid for a bit.

750
00:47:09,565 --> 00:47:12,105
It's absurd to think she'd kill herself
over something like that.

751
00:47:13,735 --> 00:47:16,235
- That's a relief.
- On the 23rd, it's Director Shin's...

752
00:47:16,975 --> 00:47:19,775
It's his birthday. Come with CEO Ha.

753
00:47:20,475 --> 00:47:22,845
Why would I go? He can go by himself.

754
00:47:22,845 --> 00:47:24,645
You two came here together late.

755
00:47:25,945 --> 00:47:27,385
Only because he asked me to come.

756
00:47:27,815 --> 00:47:28,815
I'm getting a call.

757
00:47:29,555 --> 00:47:30,555
Yes.

758
00:47:32,455 --> 00:47:34,085
If she dies, it's her own loss.

759
00:47:36,925 --> 00:47:39,825
Anything's better than being dead.

760
00:49:46,485 --> 00:49:48,825
(Surgery time, Current time,
Anesthesia time)

761
00:50:06,505 --> 00:50:09,045
Ever tried Baijiu? It's a Chinese liquor.

762
00:50:10,375 --> 00:50:11,375
No, I haven't.

763
00:50:19,155 --> 00:50:20,425
Don't bother sipping it.

764
00:50:21,355 --> 00:50:22,355
Just throw it back in one go.

765
00:50:31,495 --> 00:50:34,065
It might seem strong,
but you won't have a hangover tomorrow.

766
00:50:34,735 --> 00:50:35,735
Okay.

767
00:50:48,785 --> 00:50:50,015
Are you happy with your life?

768
00:50:51,555 --> 00:50:53,885
I'm just trying to do my best.

769
00:50:55,355 --> 00:50:56,355
I'm asking if you're happy.

770
00:50:58,425 --> 00:51:00,065
You want me to be honest?

771
00:51:00,725 --> 00:51:01,765
You should be,

772
00:51:02,735 --> 00:51:03,735
especially with a good drink like this.

773
00:51:08,405 --> 00:51:09,405
I'm struggling.

774
00:51:26,325 --> 00:51:27,325
Kim Jin Ju.

775
00:51:29,455 --> 00:51:30,455
Yes?

776
00:51:31,355 --> 00:51:32,725
Ever think about getting on
an operating table?

777
00:51:34,695 --> 00:51:37,165
If you do, I can change your life.

778
00:51:39,365 --> 00:51:41,835
Director Shin, you do plastic surgery too?

779
00:51:43,775 --> 00:51:44,875
A surgery to reshape your life.

780
00:51:47,075 --> 00:51:48,075
It's possible.

781
00:51:54,285 --> 00:51:55,715
Don't you want to live like Momo?

782
00:51:57,085 --> 00:51:58,085
As Momo.

783
00:52:00,125 --> 00:52:01,125
I'm not kidding.

784
00:52:03,995 --> 00:52:05,595
I'm going to be honest with you tonight.

785
00:52:06,995 --> 00:52:08,065
So you have to keep this a secret.

786
00:52:14,605 --> 00:52:15,605
Take it to your grave.

787
00:52:19,075 --> 00:52:20,075
Yes.

788
00:52:24,845 --> 00:52:27,215
The Momo you see now is
only Momo on the outside.

789
00:52:31,085 --> 00:52:33,985
After the accident, she was a complete...

790
00:52:40,325 --> 00:52:41,325
a complete wreck.

791
00:52:44,135 --> 00:52:45,535
How could her mother bear to see...

792
00:52:46,265 --> 00:52:47,465
her own daughter in such a state?

793
00:52:48,805 --> 00:52:51,005
And this is the world-famous Momo
we're talking about.

794
00:52:52,505 --> 00:52:53,505
So I...

795
00:52:55,245 --> 00:52:56,845
Momo's mother was the one
who suggested it,

796
00:52:58,075 --> 00:52:59,415
but regardless, I did the surgery.

797
00:53:05,385 --> 00:53:06,385
It was a success.

798
00:53:10,255 --> 00:53:11,255
But...

799
00:53:12,495 --> 00:53:13,925
people can have a change of heart.

800
00:53:15,095 --> 00:53:18,265
The plan was for me to break up with her
naturally after the brain swap,

801
00:53:22,075 --> 00:53:23,275
but now she has other ideas.

802
00:53:26,345 --> 00:53:28,175
No matter how much she looks
like Momo on the outside,

803
00:53:31,145 --> 00:53:32,145
on the inside,

804
00:53:36,515 --> 00:53:37,685
it's my future mother-in-law.

805
00:53:39,985 --> 00:53:40,985
How could that possibly work...

806
00:53:42,595 --> 00:53:43,655
from my perspective?

807
00:53:48,265 --> 00:53:49,535
I can't even imagine.

808
00:53:54,465 --> 00:53:55,475
Jin Ju.

809
00:53:57,575 --> 00:53:58,645
I'm not forcing you.

810
00:54:01,505 --> 00:54:02,875
But I want it to be you.

811
00:54:10,985 --> 00:54:13,085
Is that really possible?

812
00:54:16,355 --> 00:54:18,925
If you don't believe me,
go meet Momo and ask her some questions.

813
00:54:19,295 --> 00:54:20,395
Ask her about her old job.

814
00:54:21,095 --> 00:54:24,565
Or you could just casually part her hair
and check for the surgery scar.

815
00:54:30,235 --> 00:54:31,405
What do you think of me?

816
00:54:32,505 --> 00:54:35,145
Not as the Chairman of the orphanage
or the hospital director,

817
00:54:35,715 --> 00:54:37,545
but just as Shin Ju Shin, the man.

818
00:54:39,585 --> 00:54:40,815
Aren't you interested in finding out?

819
00:54:45,355 --> 00:54:47,725
I couldn't possibly...

820
00:54:51,025 --> 00:54:52,925
Strip away the titles,
and we're all just people.

821
00:54:53,465 --> 00:54:55,165
Just a man and a woman.

822
00:54:57,135 --> 00:54:58,195
For a while now,

823
00:54:59,965 --> 00:55:02,805
I feel like you've been slowly
finding a place in my heart.

824
00:55:03,875 --> 00:55:04,875
We're similar in a way.

825
00:55:05,775 --> 00:55:06,775
You're an orphan too.

826
00:55:07,805 --> 00:55:09,075
Now that all my family is gone...

827
00:55:12,785 --> 00:55:13,945
And with what's happened to Momo...

828
00:55:16,955 --> 00:55:17,955
I'm lonely.

829
00:55:20,485 --> 00:55:21,885
But what if it fails?

830
00:55:23,325 --> 00:55:24,525
What would happen to me then?

831
00:55:27,325 --> 00:55:28,665
I'm fine out here.

832
00:55:32,205 --> 00:55:35,305
I'm starving. You got anything to eat?
Even just some ramyeon?

833
00:55:38,745 --> 00:55:39,905
We can't afford any mistakes.

834
00:55:40,675 --> 00:55:44,445
You'll become Momo, have and enjoy
everything you've ever wanted,

835
00:55:46,185 --> 00:55:47,615
including all of her wealth,
automatically.

836
00:55:50,315 --> 00:55:53,255
So then, CEO Hyun Ran Hee
would take my body?

837
00:55:55,225 --> 00:55:58,255
If CEO Hyun's brain
were to go into your body,

838
00:55:59,525 --> 00:56:02,235
do you think she'd just accept that
and live quietly?

839
00:56:08,605 --> 00:56:09,605
Actually...

840
00:56:12,275 --> 00:56:13,275
Go on.

841
00:56:16,115 --> 00:56:18,445
A man claiming to be
my biological father showed up.

842
00:56:20,785 --> 00:56:21,785
Really?

843
00:56:38,335 --> 00:56:39,735
That smug Geum Ba Ra...

844
00:56:41,035 --> 00:56:42,875
Just you watch
what this Kim Jin Ju becomes.

845
00:56:50,115 --> 00:56:51,215
I...

846
00:56:52,315 --> 00:56:54,085
I, Kim Jin Ju...

847
00:56:55,045 --> 00:56:56,055
will become Momo.

848
00:57:05,965 --> 00:57:07,265
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

849
00:57:12,565 --> 00:57:14,805
- Hello?
- It's me.

850
00:57:16,605 --> 00:57:18,605
- Yes.
- Are you done with work?

851
00:57:19,745 --> 00:57:20,805
I'm at a work dinner.

852
00:57:21,545 --> 00:57:23,015
Then why's it so quiet?

853
00:57:23,445 --> 00:57:24,475
I'm in the bathroom.

854
00:57:25,175 --> 00:57:26,185
Okay.

855
00:57:27,215 --> 00:57:30,185
I'd like to buy you an outfit tomorrow.
Are you free?

856
00:57:32,015 --> 00:57:34,625
I feel bad that I haven't done
anything for you.

857
00:57:38,555 --> 00:57:39,895
I have a shoot that runs late.

858
00:57:42,635 --> 00:57:43,635
What about Sunday, then?

859
00:57:46,305 --> 00:57:47,335
I'll give you a call.

860
00:57:49,075 --> 00:57:50,235
We're not strangers anymore.

861
00:57:50,905 --> 00:57:52,175
You can stop being so formal.

862
00:57:54,675 --> 00:57:55,675
Okay.

863
00:57:55,745 --> 00:57:56,745
All right.

864
00:59:14,885 --> 00:59:16,095
Kim Jin Ju.

865
00:59:17,255 --> 00:59:18,895
You've lived such a sad life.

866
00:59:51,995 --> 00:59:54,465
(Power off)

867
00:59:56,995 --> 00:59:58,565
(Power off)

868
01:02:16,475 --> 01:02:17,535
Jin Ju, have a seat.

869
01:02:22,245 --> 01:02:25,075
- Does Reporter Geum like dogs?
- I think so.

870
01:02:25,445 --> 01:02:27,445
She always stops to look at dogs
when we pass them.

871
01:02:27,645 --> 01:02:29,755
What kind does she like? Small breeds?

872
01:02:30,355 --> 01:02:31,555
Or a bigger dog, like a poodle?

873
01:02:31,885 --> 01:02:32,885
Should I ask her?

874
01:02:33,355 --> 01:02:35,755
No. She even returned the painting,

875
01:02:35,825 --> 01:02:37,895
so I thought she might accept
a living gift.

876
01:02:40,725 --> 01:02:41,725
Sir.

877
01:02:42,695 --> 01:02:44,065
I'd like to take some time off.

878
01:02:45,235 --> 01:02:46,235
For how long?

879
01:02:47,565 --> 01:02:48,565
About a year.

880
01:02:49,305 --> 01:02:50,475
And that was it.

881
01:02:52,845 --> 01:02:54,345
And she got her severance pay?

882
01:02:54,405 --> 01:02:55,815
Of course.

883
01:02:57,875 --> 01:03:00,815
Did she mention meeting me?

884
01:03:01,315 --> 01:03:02,315
Not a single word.

885
01:03:02,855 --> 01:03:04,785
When she was working as Momo's stylist,

886
01:03:05,115 --> 01:03:06,485
how did the two of them get along?

887
01:03:06,825 --> 01:03:08,085
They were very close.

888
01:03:14,995 --> 01:03:15,995
Hey, Yong Joong.

889
01:03:16,365 --> 01:03:17,965
You have something tonight, don't you?

890
01:03:18,835 --> 01:03:20,805
What's with your voice? Are you sick?

891
01:03:21,335 --> 01:03:22,405
A little.

892
01:03:22,735 --> 01:03:24,105
What's wrong? Did you take anything?

893
01:03:24,235 --> 01:03:27,705
I don't really take medicine.
Why don't you come make me some porridge?

894
01:03:27,805 --> 01:03:28,975
Is the housekeeper not there?

895
01:03:29,515 --> 01:03:31,875
She's a terrible cook
when it comes to porridge.

896
01:03:44,525 --> 01:03:46,925
The passcode is the last four digits
of my phone number.

897
01:04:09,985 --> 01:04:11,055
Hey...

898
01:04:11,455 --> 01:04:12,455
Here.

899
01:04:18,155 --> 01:04:19,155
He's the one, right?

900
01:04:19,425 --> 01:04:20,425
Are you feeling better already?

901
01:04:21,095 --> 01:04:22,095
Give him a name.

902
01:04:23,365 --> 01:04:24,765
You scared me.

903
01:04:25,465 --> 01:04:28,035
I already gave him a bath,
and he's had all his shots.

904
01:04:28,305 --> 01:04:30,375
I didn't know you could pull off
a surprise like this.

905
01:04:30,775 --> 01:04:32,745
It's a birthday present
to make up for all the ones I missed.

906
01:04:38,045 --> 01:04:39,845
But I'm the only one getting gifts.

907
01:04:39,845 --> 01:04:40,915
That's what older brothers are for.

908
01:04:41,715 --> 01:04:44,415
Drop by to see him anytime.
Better yet, just move in.

909
01:04:46,485 --> 01:04:49,125
It's sweet of you to say that. Thank you.

910
01:04:49,425 --> 01:04:51,055
I mean it.

911
01:04:51,825 --> 01:04:53,325
I want to do something for you too.

912
01:04:55,365 --> 01:04:56,365
There is one thing.

913
01:04:59,535 --> 01:05:01,435
Put my mind at ease.

914
01:05:04,505 --> 01:05:06,275
I haven't done anything to worry you.

915
01:05:07,075 --> 01:05:08,745
I'll never cause you any trouble.

916
01:05:09,775 --> 01:05:11,115
Because I don't want anything from you.

917
01:05:13,385 --> 01:05:14,385
What's that supposed to mean?

918
01:05:15,415 --> 01:05:16,415
Exactly what it sounds like.

919
01:05:17,485 --> 01:05:19,555
Go on, ask for things. I can afford it.

920
01:05:20,255 --> 01:05:21,255
Just...

921
01:05:23,125 --> 01:05:24,695
having you is enough for me.

922
01:05:25,255 --> 01:05:28,525
It's incredible that I get to see you.
It's been almost 20 years.

923
01:05:32,565 --> 01:05:35,935
When I was in elementary school,
the one thing I begged my mom for...

924
01:05:36,805 --> 01:05:38,975
was a little sister.

925
01:05:39,545 --> 01:05:42,105
But she'd just give me a vague smile
and brush me off.

926
01:05:42,745 --> 01:05:44,375
Looking back on it now,

927
01:05:44,875 --> 01:05:48,615
my mom was over 40.
I guess she didn't think she could do it.

928
01:05:49,045 --> 01:05:51,415
If she'd explained it better,
I would've gotten it.

929
01:05:52,855 --> 01:05:55,555
She underestimated her son's maturity.

930
01:05:56,725 --> 01:05:58,825
So how could I not be completely smitten
with my little one?

931
01:05:59,225 --> 01:06:00,225
At first sight?

932
01:06:02,395 --> 01:06:03,935
I'm about to turn 30.

933
01:06:04,265 --> 01:06:05,535
Don't I age too?

934
01:06:06,635 --> 01:06:07,635
To me,

935
01:06:08,805 --> 01:06:10,735
you'll always be that little kid
from the corner store.

936
01:06:21,985 --> 01:06:25,385
In a past life, we must've been
brother and sister,

937
01:06:25,755 --> 01:06:27,385
or maybe a father and daughter?

938
01:06:28,055 --> 01:06:29,125
You believe in past lives?

939
01:06:29,895 --> 01:06:31,825
Logically, it makes sense that they do.

940
01:06:35,065 --> 01:06:37,065
I guess I must've committed a lot of sins
in my past life.

941
01:06:37,465 --> 01:06:39,805
People would swear at you for saying that.

942
01:06:39,865 --> 01:06:41,005
They'd ask if you've looked in a mirror.

943
01:06:44,135 --> 01:06:45,475
Focus on what you have.

944
01:06:48,275 --> 01:06:49,275
You've got me.

945
01:06:50,575 --> 01:06:52,545
You're my everything.

946
01:06:54,245 --> 01:06:55,315
But don't feel pressured.

947
01:06:56,015 --> 01:06:57,815
Pressured? We confessed
our feelings to each other.

948
01:07:00,825 --> 01:07:03,255
The housekeeper left a whole feast for us.

949
01:07:19,705 --> 01:07:21,045
It's not your birthday, though.

950
01:07:21,345 --> 01:07:22,575
It's your belated birthday dinner.

951
01:07:25,175 --> 01:07:28,015
You've already had plenty to eat.
All you can do is watch.

952
01:07:29,245 --> 01:07:31,185
I told her to make it
a kid's birthday meal.

953
01:07:33,255 --> 01:07:35,685
You're not wired like other guys.

954
01:07:36,525 --> 01:07:38,995
Is that a compliment?
Are you saying I'm androgynous?

955
01:07:40,425 --> 01:07:43,135
It means you were raised right.

956
01:07:43,835 --> 01:07:46,135
You're considerate and thoughtful.

957
01:07:46,565 --> 01:07:48,065
I was raised right,

958
01:07:48,505 --> 01:07:50,375
but I went through a serious angsty phase
as a freshman.

959
01:07:51,575 --> 01:07:53,275
Do you look just like your dad?

960
01:07:53,275 --> 01:07:55,145
Not at all.
I'll show you a photo after we eat.

961
01:07:56,475 --> 01:07:58,615
- I should heat up the soup.
- It's okay. I don't like it too hot.

962
01:07:58,875 --> 01:08:00,545
Seaweed soup is fine
when it's not super hot.

963
01:08:07,285 --> 01:08:08,285
Hey...

964
01:08:09,595 --> 01:08:11,695
I don't want to lose you
to some other woman.

965
01:08:12,455 --> 01:08:13,465
You're too good for them.

966
01:08:13,765 --> 01:08:14,995
Then just keep me by your side forever.

967
01:08:15,265 --> 01:08:16,335
I'm serious.

968
01:08:18,095 --> 01:08:19,095
Even if I get married,

969
01:08:19,635 --> 01:08:21,635
how I feel about my kiddo
will never change.

970
01:08:22,805 --> 01:08:25,075
Does he not see me as a woman at all?

971
01:08:35,145 --> 01:08:36,685
Your housekeeper is an amazing cook.

972
01:08:37,755 --> 01:08:40,055
I specifically asked for marinated beef
instead of the braised ribs.

973
01:08:41,025 --> 01:08:43,995
Because when I was a kid,
I thought marinated beef was tastier.

974
01:08:44,355 --> 01:08:45,495
And now you prefer the ribs?

975
01:08:45,795 --> 01:08:46,795
Steak.

976
01:08:47,995 --> 01:08:48,995
Royal court rice cakes.

977
01:08:51,595 --> 01:08:53,805
- Are these rice or wheat cakes?
- Rice cakes.

978
01:08:53,905 --> 01:08:55,235
I like the rice cakes, too.

979
01:09:04,415 --> 01:09:05,445
Ever since I met you again,

980
01:09:06,945 --> 01:09:08,185
I've been so happy.

981
01:09:16,425 --> 01:09:17,425
I'm the one who should be saying that.

982
01:09:19,325 --> 01:09:20,365
What are you going to name him?

983
01:09:25,535 --> 01:09:26,535
Pickles.

984
01:09:30,375 --> 01:09:33,375
Have you heard from Director Shin?
About a birthday invite.

985
01:09:34,105 --> 01:09:35,105
No.

986
01:09:35,845 --> 01:09:37,245
Momo said she was going to invite you.

987
01:09:38,615 --> 01:09:39,915
Ju Shin hates that stuff.

988
01:09:40,845 --> 01:09:43,055
He hasn't celebrated his birthday
since his mother passed away.

989
01:09:45,585 --> 01:09:49,525
Before his mother passed away,
what was Director Shin like?

990
01:09:49,795 --> 01:09:50,955
Do people ever really change?

991
01:09:51,225 --> 01:09:54,295
Even back then, was he blunt?
If that's a nice way of putting it.

992
01:09:55,065 --> 01:09:56,125
What would be a bad way of putting it?

993
01:09:57,065 --> 01:09:58,365
There's nothing bad, really.

994
01:09:58,465 --> 01:10:01,435
He may not be warm,
but he's not one to look down on people.

995
01:11:32,895 --> 01:11:35,665
(Doctor Shin)

996
01:11:35,895 --> 01:11:37,765
You're with some other guy right now.

997
01:11:38,965 --> 01:11:40,365
You must be here to run
an errand for my guy.

998
01:11:40,365 --> 01:11:41,435
Here to pick something up?

999
01:11:41,535 --> 01:11:43,535
Don't you ever think
Geum Ba Ra is a little too smart?

1000
01:11:43,775 --> 01:11:44,805
What's wrong with being smart?

1001
01:11:44,805 --> 01:11:48,205
I see Ba Ra as a sister, not a woman.

1002
01:11:48,305 --> 01:11:50,145
Do you think she feels the same way?

1003
01:11:50,245 --> 01:11:52,045
- Can you video call?
- Yes.

1004
01:11:52,745 --> 01:11:54,185
Look at me and go potty.

1005
01:11:54,185 --> 01:11:55,615
My love has begun...

1006
01:11:56,085 --> 01:11:57,455
with Director Shin Ju Shin.

1007
01:11:57,715 --> 01:11:59,455
Do you think I could get an MRI?

1008
01:11:59,455 --> 01:12:00,585
Are you feeling unwell?

1009
01:12:01,385 --> 01:12:02,985
Email me Geum Ba Ra's files.

1010
01:12:03,255 --> 01:12:05,125
- All of them.
- Understood.

1011
01:12:05,195 --> 01:12:06,465
What are your thoughts on a brain swap?

1012
01:12:06,725 --> 01:12:07,765
Have you ever thought about it?

1013
01:12:07,825 --> 01:12:10,565
You mean how they say AI can replace
an entire human brain?

1014
01:12:10,635 --> 01:12:11,635
The face would stay the same.

1015
01:12:12,735 --> 01:12:14,265
If we could swap only the brain...

1016
01:12:14,405 --> 01:12:16,405
You mean you, Director?

1017
01:12:21,905 --> 01:12:23,915
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
